name: Cape Cod Biscuits
author: MARY A. PUTMAN
summary: This is a different change of pace from ordinary biscuits, colorful for the holidays, and so easy to make.
ingredients: ⅓ cup whole berry cranberry sauce
directions: Preheat an oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C)
Use a fork to lightly blend the biscuit mix and milk in a large bowl
With spoon, drop 16 biscuits onto prepared baking sheet
Make a small depression in the center of each biscuit
Bake in preheated oven until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes
Just before serving, evenly fill the depression in each biscuit with cranberry sauce
